title: SFH on mental health services and medical products recall
content_text:
p>
    Following is the transcript of remarks (English portion) by the Secretary 
    for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, after attending the opening ceremony of 
    Hospital Authority Convention 2010 today (May 10): Reporter: (on mental health services)  Secretary for Food and Health: The policy of mental health has already been 
    undergoing continuous review over the last few years. The Government has 
    also increased resources to this particular service. If I remember 
    correctly, last year we have increased $30 million. And this year we will be

correctly, last year we have increased $30 million. And this year we will be 
    increasing about $100 million in various sectors, particularly in the 
    community service, both increasing doctors, mental health nurses as well as 
    social workers. The important element is how to coordinate the various 
    services, both from the hospitals and the mental health clinics, all the way 
    to the social workers, the non-government organisations and so on in the 
    community. Another area to consider is how we can support the family members

community. Another area to consider is how we can support the family members 
    as well as the community, be the residents or the neighbours in case they 
    discover somebody who is out of mind in term of their behaviour, whether 
    some of our social workers or our professionals can intervene them as early 
    as possible.  Reporter: (on Quality Pharmaceutical Laboratory Ltd) Secretary for Food and Health: As far as I know, the Department of Health 
    has already suspended the operation of this particular company, asked them

has already suspended the operation of this particular company, asked them 
    to provide the documentations and all the details of how they manufacture 
    the drugs so that they can follow up. We will not allow any of the products 
    to be sold or being utilised in the market right now.  Reporter: (on drugs for Age-related Macular Degeneration) Secretary for Food and Health: As far as I know, according to the 
    ophthalmologist that I have enquired, this is basically the same drug that

ophthalmologist that I have enquired, this is basically the same drug that 
    is under two particular brand names. One is being patented for the treatment 
    of cancer and the other one is patented for treatment of a macular disease. 
    In fact, they are the same drug. In many other foreign countries and 
    research centres, these drugs are being used for the same disease. According 
    to the existing arrangement, if any of the drugs, that I have so-called off 
    labeled, they need to have some supervision and that is the reason why the

labeled, they need to have some supervision and that is the reason why the Hospital Authority now wants to coordinate a research project with the universities to ensure that it will apply Avastin to patients with Wet Aged-related Macular Degeneration under the proper supervision and also with full knowledge of the patients. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript)
